---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-coverage', text: 'Plans and Coverage', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pros-and-cons', text: 'Pros and Cons', level: 2 },
  { id: 'claims-and-service', text: 'Claims and Service', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-its-for', text: 'Who It\'s For', level: 2 },
  { id: 'alternatives', text: 'Alternatives to Consider', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Aetna vs GeoBlue', href: '/compare/aetna-international-vs-geoblue' },
  { title: 'Aetna vs Cigna', href: '/compare/cigna-global-vs-aetna-international' },
  { title: 'Aetna vs BUPA', href: '/compare/bupa-global-vs-aetna-international' },
  { title: 'Best Expat Insurance', href: '/best/expat-health-insurance' },
  { title: 'Aetna in Mexico', href: '/countries/mexico/insurance/aetna-international' },
  { title: 'Aetna in Spain', href: '/countries/spain/insurance/aetna-international' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage' },
  { key: 'annualMax', header: 'Annual Maximum' },
  { key: 'bestFor', header: 'Best For' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Pioneer', coverage: 'Inpatient + Emergency', annualMax: '$1M', bestFor: 'Major medical protection' },
  { plan: 'Pioneer Prime', coverage: 'Pioneer + Outpatient', annualMax: '$2M', bestFor: 'Comprehensive care' },
  { plan: 'Pioneer Platinum', coverage: 'Prime + Enhanced', annualMax: '$5M', bestFor: 'Premium coverage' },
  { plan: 'Navigator', coverage: 'Flexible modular', annualMax: 'Up to $5M', bestFor: 'Customized coverage' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Aetna International Review"
  description="In-depth review of Aetna International health insurance. Coverage, pricing, pros and cons for expats needing US and global coverage."
  headline="Aetna International Health Insurance Review"
  subheadline="A detailed look at Aetna International's plans, pricing, and why it's the go-to choice for US expats needing seamless stateside coverage."
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get an Aetna Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>
    Aetna International is a division of Aetna, now part of CVS Health—one of the largest healthcare companies in the United States. For US expats, Aetna International offers something competitors struggle to match: seamless integration with the US healthcare system.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you're an American living abroad who needs to maintain access to US doctors and hospitals (whether for specialist care, family visits, or eventual repatriation), Aetna International should be on your shortlist.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Quick Facts</h3>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
      <li><strong>Parent Company:</strong> CVS Health / Aetna</li>
      <li><strong>Headquarters:</strong> London, UK (international operations)</li>
      <li><strong>Countries Covered:</strong> 190+</li>
      <li><strong>Network Providers:</strong> 1.7 million+ (including US Aetna network)</li>
      <li><strong>US Coverage:</strong> Full integration with domestic Aetna network</li>
      <li><strong>Plan Types:</strong> Pioneer, Navigator series</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get a Personalized Quote"
    description="See what Aetna International would cost for your situation."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="plans-and-coverage">Plans and Coverage</h2>
  <p>
    Aetna International offers two main product lines: the Pioneer series (tiered plans) and the Navigator series (modular/customizable plans).
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Pioneer Series</h3>
  <p>
    The Pioneer plans are straightforward tiered options:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Pioneer:</strong> Inpatient, emergency, and medical evacuation. No outpatient.</li>
    <li><strong>Pioneer Prime:</strong> Adds outpatient care, prescriptions, and wellness benefits.</li>
    <li><strong>Pioneer Platinum:</strong> Enhanced limits, dental, vision, and maternity included.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Navigator Series</h3>
  <p>
    Navigator plans let you build your own coverage by selecting modules:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Core hospital coverage (required base)</li>
    <li>Outpatient module</li>
    <li>Dental module</li>
    <li>Vision module</li>
    <li>Maternity module</li>
    <li>Wellness module</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    This modular approach is useful if you want comprehensive hospital coverage but don't need dental, or want to add maternity without upgrading your entire plan.
  </p>

  <h3>Core Coverage (All Plans)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Hospital stays and surgeries</li>
    <li>Emergency treatment worldwide</li>
    <li>Cancer treatment and chronic disease management</li>
    <li>Medical evacuation (up to $1M)</li>
    <li>Repatriation of remains</li>
    <li>Mental health coverage (inpatient)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>The US Coverage Advantage</h3>
  <p>
    Unlike most international insurers that treat US coverage as an expensive add-on, Aetna International provides integrated access to Aetna's domestic US network. This means:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Direct billing at US hospitals and clinics</li>
    <li>Access to Aetna's negotiated rates</li>
    <li>No separate "US coverage" tier to purchase</li>
    <li>Seamless care when visiting family or relocating back</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    Aetna International pricing varies by age, plan tier, coverage area, and deductible. Plans including US coverage are priced accordingly but often more competitive than adding US coverage to other international plans.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Estimated monthly premiums (including US coverage):</strong>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Age 35, Pioneer Prime: $280-380/month</li>
    <li>Age 45, Pioneer Prime: $380-500/month</li>
    <li>Age 55, Pioneer Prime: $520-700/month</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    <strong>Excluding US coverage</strong> reduces premiums by approximately 30-40%.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Deductible options:</strong> $0, $250, $500, $1,000, $2,500, $5,000. Higher deductibles can reduce premiums by 15-30%.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Price Comparison Note</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800">
      When comparing Aetna to Cigna or Allianz, factor in the US coverage cost. Adding US coverage to those plans often costs 40-60% more. Aetna's integrated US pricing can make it more competitive for expats who need stateside access.
    </p>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="See Your Actual Price"
    description="Get a quote based on your age, location, and coverage needs."
    buttonText="Get a Quote"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
  />

  <h2 id="pros-and-cons">Pros and Cons</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Pros</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
        <li>Best-in-class US coverage integration</li>
        <li>Access to 1.7M+ providers including US Aetna network</li>
        <li>Modular Navigator plans for customization</li>
        <li>Strong corporate/employer plan options</li>
        <li>CVS Health backing (financial stability)</li>
        <li>Good mental health coverage</li>
        <li>24/7 multilingual support</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-red-900 mb-3">Cons</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-red-800">
        <li>Higher premiums than some competitors</li>
        <li>Less competitive without US coverage needs</li>
        <li>Pre-existing conditions typically excluded</li>
        <li>Maternity has 12-month waiting period</li>
        <li>Some plans have area-of-coverage restrictions</li>
        <li>Less brand recognition outside US market</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="claims-and-service">Claims and Service</h2>

  <h3>Filing Claims</h3>
  <p>
    Aetna International offers multiple claims submission options:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Online member portal</li>
    <li>Mobile app (Aetna International)</li>
    <li>Email submission</li>
    <li>Direct billing at network providers</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Claims are typically processed within 5-10 business days. Direct billing is available at network hospitals worldwide, including the full US Aetna network.
  </p>

  <h3>Customer Service</h3>
  <p>
    24/7 support is available via phone, email, and online chat. Support is offered in multiple languages including English, Spanish, French, and Mandarin.
  </p>
  <p>
    Aetna International also provides dedicated case management for complex medical situations and coordinates care across countries when needed.
  </p>

  <h3>Member Tools</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Online provider search (global + US networks)</li>
    <li>Digital ID cards</li>
    <li>Claims tracking</li>
    <li>Pre-authorization requests</li>
    <li>Telehealth services (select plans)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="who-its-for">Who It's For</h2>
  <p>
    Aetna International is a strong choice if you:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Are a US citizen/resident living abroad</li>
    <li>Need regular access to US healthcare</li>
    <li>Visit the US frequently for family or business</li>
    <li>Plan to eventually repatriate to the US</li>
    <li>Work for a US company with international assignments</li>
    <li>Want one plan that works seamlessly in both locations</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    It may not be ideal if you:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Don't need US coverage (other plans may be cheaper)</li>
    <li>Are on a strict budget</li>
    <li>Are not connected to the US healthcare system</li>
    <li>Prefer European-based insurers (for EU expats)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="alternatives">Alternatives to Consider</h2>
  <p>
    Depending on your needs, these alternatives might be worth comparing:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Similar network size, strong service, but US coverage costs more. <a href="/providers/cigna-global">Read our review</a></li>
    <li><strong>GeoBlue:</strong> Another US-focused option with Blue Cross network access. Good for Americans who want domestic continuity.</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Better value if you don't need US coverage. EU-based. <a href="/providers/allianz-care">Read our review</a></li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Premium option with mental health parity. <a href="/providers/bupa-global">Read our review</a></li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready to Compare?"
    description="See how Aetna International stacks up for your specific needs."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This review is for informational purposes only. Plan details, pricing, and availability change. We are not affiliated with Aetna International and are not insurance brokers. Verify all information directly with Aetna before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
